每週課程內容及預計進度 Weekly scheduled progress




　　　　　　　　
Tentative Syllabus:Week 01 (Feb. 28): National Holiday (No Class)Week 02 (Mar. 07): Narrating: Introduction and In-Class Practice; Sample Reading Elizabeth Wong’s “The Struggle to Be an All-American Girl.”Week 03 (Mar. 14): Describing: Introduction and In-Class Practice; Sample Reading Maxine Hong Kingston’s “Catfish in the Bathtub”; The Elements of Style (PP.1-14) Week 04 (Mar. 21): Ditto; TOEFL Grammar Test; *The First Paper Due.Week 05 (Mar. 28): Illustration: Introduction and In-Class Practice; Sample Reading Lewis Thomas’s “Death in the Open”; The Elements of Style (PP.15-33) Week 06 (Apr. 04): Spring Vacation (No Class)Week 07 (Apr.11): Comparison and Contrast: Introduction and In-Class Practice; Sample Reading Rachel Carson’s “A Fable for Tomorrow”; *The Second Paper Due. Week 08 (Apr. 18 ): Classifying: Introduction and In-Class Practice; Sample Reading E.B. White’s “The Three New Yorks”; TOEFL Grammar TestWeek 09 (Apr. 25): Midterm Exam; *The Third Paper Due Week 10 (May 02 ): Defining: Introduction and In-Class Practice; Sample Reading Suzanne Britt Jordan’s “Fun, Oh Boy. Fun You could die.”Week 12 (May 16): Ditto; The Elements of Style (PP.34-66)Week 13 (May 23): Cause-and-Effect Analysis: Introduction and In-Class Practice; Sample Reading  Linda Bird Frank’s “The Ambivalence of Abortion.” Week 14 (May 30): Ditto; TOEFL Grammar Test; * The Fourth Paper Due. Week 15 (Jun. 06): Argumentation and Persuasion: Introduction and In-ClassPractice; Sample Reading Judy Syfers “I want a Wife.”Week 16 (Jun. 13): Ditto; The Elements of Style (PP.67-86) Week 17 (Jun. 20): Personal MeetingWeek 18 (Jun.27): * Final Paper Due.




